  "response": "In many countries, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain sectors are typically obligated to report suspicious transactions or activities to designated authorities. Specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but often include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Identifying and documenting suspicious transactions\n3. Conducting customer due diligence\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Training employees to recognize potential money laundering\n\nHowever, I want to be clear that I cannot provide specific legal advice about money laundering reporting requirements.",
